    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @Maaark, I just made a showMorePaginator widget that you can see in action here: http://codepen.io/vvo/pen/jAwXoo\n\nHere's the code:\n\n``` js\nvar paginatorShowMore = {\n  init: function(args) {\n    var helper = args.helper;\n    document\n      .querySelector('#show-more')\n      .addEventListener('click', function() {\n        helper\n          .setQueryParameter('hitsPerPage',\n          helper.getQueryParameter('hitsPerPage') + defaultHitsPerPage\n        )\n        .search();\n      });\n  },\n  render: function(args) {\n    var helper = args.helper;\n    var currentHitsPerPage = helper.getQueryParameter('hitsPerPage');\n    if (currentHitsPerPage > defaultHitsPerPage) {\n      var hitsIndexToScroll = currentHitsPerPage - defaultHitsPerPage;\n      document\n        .querySelectorAll('.ais-hits--item')\n        [hitsIndexToScroll].scrollIntoView();\n        // if we are showing 50 hits, make sure\n        // the 39th hit is visible in the viewport\n        // this also handles url refresh/url copy paste\n    }\n  }\n};\n\nsearch.addWidget(paginatorShowMore);\n```\n\nYou should be able to throw a lot of your ccurrent code, let me know how it goes.\n",
